<entity>
	<entityName>vegPlot.PLOTOBSERVATION</entityName>
	<entitySummary>This table stores plot information that may vary between sampling events.</entitySummary>
	<entityDescription>Recognizing that a plot may be resampled and that some of the environmental
	conditions may change between resampling events the database design has changed to accomodate this.  
	Now all attributes that are percieved to potentially change on the order of a decade are stored in the 
	plotObservation table whereas those attributes deemed to be regular in time/space are stored in the plot 
	table.
	</entityDescription>
